<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0011183> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "Corpus spongiosum (also known as corpus cavernosum urethrae in older texts) is the mass of spongy tissue surrounding the male urethra within the penis." .
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0011183> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBPROP_0000009> "The function of the corpus spongiosum in erection is to prevent the urethra from pinching closed, thereby maintaining the urethra as a viable channel for ejaculation. To do this, the corpus spongiosum remains pliable during erection while the corpora cavernosum penis becomes engorged with blood." .
